3️⃣ End-to-End Data Flow (🔥 MOST IMPORTANT)
What Happens When You Open Google?

Let’s connect everything you learned:

Step-by-Step Flow

1️⃣ Enter google.com
→ DNS converts to IP

2️⃣ TCP handshake
→ connection established

3️⃣ HTTP request sent
→ GET request

4️⃣ Routing
→ packet travels across internet

5️⃣ Server processes request

6️⃣ Response sent back

7️⃣ Browser displays page

Mental Model

Like ordering food online:

search restaurant
connect
place order
delivery
Why It Works

Each concept you learned plays a role:

DNS → find server
TCP → reliable connection
HTTP → communication
Routing → path
Memory Trick

DNS → TCP → HTTP → Routing → Response

4️⃣ Common Interview Traps 🔥
Trap 1

❌ “IP identifies device completely”
✔ Actually → Port identifies application

Trap 2

❌ “TCP is always better”
✔ No → depends on use case

Trap 3

❌ “HTTP is secure”
✔ Only HTTPS is secure

Trap 4

❌ “MAC works globally”
✔ Only within local network

Golden Tip 🧠

Interviewers test concept clarity, not definitions

